  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Pakistan flood death toll surpasses 1,000",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the figures released by Pakistan's National Disaster Management Authority, the death toll from monsoon floods in Pakistan since June has reached 1,033.",
        "119 people have died in the last 24 hours, and more than 33 million people have been affected by heavy rains since June, which continue to lash parts of the country.",
        "More than four million people have been affected by rising water levels, the government said, as thousands evacuated Pakistan's northern regions under an order on Saturday.",
        "An official in Sindh, a province in the south-east of the country, said the floods were worse than in 2010 and could be considered one of the worst in Pakistan's history.",
        "The 2010 floods killed at least 1,700 people across Pakistan, most of them from Sindh."
      ],
